Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mild anemia (low hemoglobin and erythrocyte count) with normal MCV and MCH, suggesting normocytic, normochromic anemia. Glucose is slightly below normal, but HbA1c is within target, indicating overall good glycemic control. Platelet count is normal, but platelet distribution width is elevated, possibly reflecting increased platelet size variability. Renal and electrolyte parameters are within normal limits. No acute abnormalities detected; recommend clinical correlation for anemia.
